# Revamp Project Management Bento Box Demonstration

The current `ProjectManagementPreview` component in `LandingFeatures.tsx` only demonstrates connecting a single Ads account to a project. To provide a "better and more dynamic demonstration on how we help user connect many Google Ads account into a project management suite, where they can input their actual ref count earned and make sense of all analytics", we will overhaul this component.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since this introduces a change to the User Experience, PRD documentation will also be synchronized to adhere to the "No Spec, No Service" and the "Living Document Rule". Are you satisfied with the proposed visual flow below?

## Visual Flow Design

We will replace the single-card modal sequence with a "mini-dashboard" split layout (still fitting within the 220px Bento Box height):
1. **Left Sidebar (Accounts List):** Dynamically populates with multiple Ads Accounts (e.g., "NA Campaigns", "EU Campaigns").
2. **Right Panel (Analytics & Input):** 
   - Displays aggregated Ad Spend from the multiple connected accounts.
   - Shows an automated typing sequence where a user "inputs" the aggregated Ref Count.
   - Features dynamic metric cards (like True CPA and ROI) that recalculate instantaneously once the Ref Count is updated, emphasizing the analytical power.
3. This entire flow will utilize `framer-motion` to smoothly sequence the connections, typing, and metric reveals while maintaining the monochrome, premium aesthetic.

